Key Match Events: Pakistan lost Saim Ayub early on
Babar Azam and Mohammad Rizwan stitched a stand of 139 runs
Pakistan clinched the series with 6 wickets to spare
Post-Match Reflections: Babar Azam said the Irish batters were batting brilliantly in the first half but his bowlers put pressure by taking few wickets
Lorcan Tucker said the platform was set for a big score but unfortunately it didn't come off
Shaheen Afridi won the Player of the Match award and said the bowlers tried to hit good lines and lengths
Miscellaneous Highlights: An easy and comfortable couple of games for Pakistan to seal the series
Ireland were well below the par score
Pakistan made a mockery of the chase
